    <div class="collapsible-header">Does SPI Borescopes come in different lengths? How long can they be made?</div>
    <div class="collapsible-body"><p>The SPI-Flex Series and Specialty Series Scopes are available in sizes up to 100 meters (328 feet). The SPI-AVB Articulating Video Borescopes are available in sizes from 1 meter to 4 meters in length (3.28′ – 13.12′ Feet).</p></div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <div class="collapsible-header">Are they waterproof?</div>
    <div class="collapsible-body"><p>All SPI Borescopes are drip and splash proof. The SPI-WPB (Water-Proof Borescope), SPI-PLB (Pipe and Pipe Line Borescope) and the SPI-HPB (Heat-Proof Borescope) are all waterproof.</p></div>
  </li>
  <li>
    <div class="collapsible-header">What is a safe temperature range to operate SPI Borescopes in?</div>
    <div class="collapsible-body"><p>The SPI-HPB (Heat-Proof Borescope) can operate in temperatures up to 250°C (480°F). All others should be used in the average operating temperature range. Ask a consultant for details.</p></div>
  </li>
